						<summary>

						<p>On a broken slab in the dilapidated Subrahmaṇya temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Kaṉṉaradēva Year 21: 960 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged. It records the gift of one hundred and eighty <hi rend="italic">nāḻi</hi> of oil per year to be supplied to the god, Mahādēva of Tiruviḻichchil in Āmūr-kōṭṭam, at the rate of sixty <hi rend="italic">nāḻi</hi> of oil during the months of <hi rend="italic">Māśi, [Kārttigai]</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Aippasi.</hi> Other details are lost. </p>						

						</summary>
